reviewText:
The game starts as something that looks good, but soon you realize the controls are bad like...quite bad. Most of the jumps over spikes I failed them lots of times because it's like the square is going on ice: it doesn't stop when you stop pressing A or W keys, it keeps moving for a few more inches, even when you jump (also, it never jumps when you press the spacebar; it takes a few seconds to get the memo), and that always ends up in your death.

At some point, this problem got in the way really bad: it wasn't that the platform level was very hard, it was that the controls didn't respond like they have to, so I kept dying because I couldn't control the square properly.

EDIT: scratch that. Some levels are impossible. I've tried most of them, and a lot of them the game doesn't give you an explanation: it just expect you to find out why the exit point is bouncing so fast, or why is going away from you, or some levels where everything is prepared so bad you can't pass them no matter what you try.

I'm afraid I won't play it again.

reviewText: Escape is a very simplistic rage platforming game and it's also free, but is it worth your time ? To answer the question no it's not. Escape is a rage platformer where the goal is simple you need to get to the portal at the end of the level without dying. This game also has puzzles but a lot of them are quite stupid when you do figure out what the solution was. The game requires a lot of perfect jumps and with the really crappy controls it's not really possible. Those jumps will happen only by dumb luck or the game bug's out and let's you win. Some of the puzzles are really stupid and to explain and the hints the game gives you barely make any sense. Overall for a free game this game is nothing really special. Terrible controls, bad level design and no music or sound effects really make this game nothing special. Only play this game if you're incredibly bored otherwise skip this game. I give Escape a 4/10

reviewText:
I think I can't add new information or insight, but I can confirm a few points.

This game got some good ideas worked into it. Actually, as a small, fun puzzle game, this would have been pretty nice. The problem lays in the platformer part. The controls are rather fitting and flowy, but - as other pointed out already - the wonky collisions tend to make a handful of levels unbelievably frustrating.

As a free game however it's a great pastime. Levels are skipable, too, so you may spend a few minutes on the ones you like. The game is not long - most levels are finished in a few seconds - but interesting enough to give it a try.
In the end, you wouldn't lose much.

reviewText:
A nice little game to play when you're bored. If you choose to download this, make sure you enable vSync for it (you'll have to do it through your graphics driver's control panel) otherwise the game is literally unplayable.

Pros:
- Fun
- Good puzzle aspect in some parts
- Great ending (seriously, if nothing else, just download it for the ending)
- You can skip levels
- Free (obviously)

Cons:
- Ledge hitboxes are strange. Despite being depicted as right angles, they actually have curved hitboxes that you can slide off of. I'm not sure whether this was intentional or not, but I'll give the creator the benefit of the doubt.
- The game is extremely short and has little to no replay value, but it's up to debate whether this is a con because of the rage this game is capable of producing.
- Controls aren't as tight as I would like. Your character (square, whatever) feels very slidey, making it hard to land in very specific locations.

Final verdict: 7/10

tl;dr: The game is worth downloading, just make sure you enable vSync in your graphics driver's control panel.
